---
import LandingLayout from '../layouts/LandingLayout.astro';

const sidebarGroups = [
  ['Start here', ['Introduction', 'Quickstart', 'Concepts', 'FAQ']],
  ['The capture loop', ['Search before planning', 'Capturing work', 'Trigger phrases', 'Naming records']],
  ['Records', ['Decisions', 'Reviews', 'Learnings', 'Repo profiles', 'Tool notes', 'Frontmatter reference']],
  ['Live tasks', ['BGT-NNNN files', 'Status & priority', 'Dependencies', 'Activity log']],
  ['Agents', ['Claude', 'Codex', 'ChatGPT', 'Gemini CLI', 'Custom entrypoints']],
  ['Workflows', ['Indexing a repo', 'Cleaning memory', 'Retrieving context']],
  ['Dashboard', ['Overview', 'Task queue', 'Dependency graph']],
];
---

<LandingLayout title="Docs | Braingent">
  <header class="docs-nav">
    <div class="left">
      <a class="nav-brand" href="/" style="font-size: 19px;">
        <img class="mark" src="/braingent_logo.svg" alt="" width="24" height="24" />
        Braingent
      </a>
      <span class="docs-version">DOCS · v0.1</span>
    </div>
    <div class="docs-search" aria-label="Search placeholder">
      <span aria-hidden="true">⌕</span>
      Search records, decisions, workflows...
      <span class="kbd">⌘ K</span>
    </div>
    <div class="docs-toplinks">
      <a href="/">← Landing</a>
      <a href="https://github.com/thedoublejay/braingent-manifesto">GitHub</a>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="docs-shell">
    <aside class="sidebar" aria-label="Docs navigation">
      {
        sidebarGroups.map(([title, items]) => (
          <div class="sidebar-group">
            <h6>{title}</h6>
            <ul>
              {(items as string[]).map((item, index) => (
                <li><a class={item === 'Capturing work' ? 'current' : ''} href={index === 0 ? '/guides/getting-started/' : '#'}>{item}</a></li>
              ))}
            </ul>
          </div>
        ))
      }
    </aside>

    <main class="docs-main">
      <nav class="breadcrumb" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
        <a href="/docs/">Docs</a>
        <span class="sep">/</span>
        <a href="#">The capture loop</a>
        <span class="sep">/</span>
        <span>Capturing work</span>
      </nav>

      <h1>Capturing work</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">How a finished task becomes a durable record.</p>
      <div class="badge-row">
        <span class="badge ok">● Stable</span>
        <span class="badge">Updated 2026-05-06</span>
        <span class="badge warn">Manifesto v0.1</span>
      </div>

      <p>
        Capture is the moment a session leaves something behind. The agent has
        done the work, you have reviewed it, and a Markdown record gets written
        with frontmatter, evidence, and follow-ups. Future sessions search that
        record before they plan.
      </p>
      <p>
        This scaffold keeps the design shell in place while the final docs
        content is synthesized from the manifesto source material.
      </p>

      <div class="callout">
        <span class="label">Rule of thumb</span>
        <p>If a future you, or a future agent, would benefit from knowing why this happened, capture it.</p>
      </div>

      <h2 id="when">When to capture</h2>
      <p>Capture after meaningful work concludes, not for every small edit.</p>
      <ul>
        <li>A non-obvious decision was made.</li>
        <li>A review surfaced something worth remembering.</li>
        <li>A debugging session ended with a reusable learning.</li>
        <li>A live task reaches done, shipped, or abandoned.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 id="triggers">Trigger phrases</h2>
      <div class="triggers">
        <div class="trigger"><code>save to braingent</code><p>Create a durable record.</p></div>
        <div class="trigger"><code>capture this</code><p>Normalize the useful context.</p></div>
        <div class="trigger"><code>done thanks</code><p>Close out substantive work.</p></div>
      </div>

      <h2 id="anatomy">Anatomy of a capture</h2>
      <pre class="docs-code"><code><span class="yaml-key">title:</span> <span class="yaml-val">Scaffold Braingent website</span>
<span class="yaml-key">record_kind:</span> <span class="yaml-val">task</span>
<span class="yaml-key">status:</span> <span class="yaml-val">completed</span>
<span class="yaml-key">date:</span> <span class="yaml-val">2026-05-06</span>

<span class="md-h">## Goal</span>
<span class="md-bullet">-</span> Build the public website scaffold.

<span class="md-h">## Evidence</span>
<span class="md-bullet">-</span> Build passed.
<span class="comment"># Keep source links and verification close to the claim.</span></code></pre>

      <h3 id="naming">File naming</h3>
      <p>Use dated, lowercase filenames so records sort naturally and search well.</p>

      <h3 id="commit">Commit message</h3>
      <p>Keep commits scoped to the logical step that changed the memory or website.</p>

      <h2 id="never">What never gets captured</h2>
      <p>Secrets, credentials, private keys, raw tokens, and sensitive personal data do not belong in memory.</p>

      <div class="docs-pager">
        <a class="pager-link" href="/guides/getting-started/"><span class="dir">Previous</span><span class="title">Getting started</span></a>
        <a class="pager-link next" href="/guides/cli-workflows/"><span class="dir">Next</span><span class="title">CLI workflows</span></a>
      </div>
    </main>

    <aside class="toc" aria-label="On this page">
      <h6>On this page</h6>
      <ul>
        <li><a class="current" href="#when">When to capture</a></li>
        <li><a href="#triggers">Trigger phrases</a></li>
        <li><a href="#anatomy">Anatomy of a capture</a></li>
        <li><a href="#naming">File naming</a></li>
        <li><a href="#commit">Commit message</a></li>
        <li><a href="#never">What never gets captured</a></li>
      </ul>
      <div class="docs-meta">
        <a href="https://github.com/thedoublejay/braingent-manifesto">Edit this page on GitHub →</a>
        <a href="https://github.com/thedoublejay/braingent-manifesto/issues">Report an issue</a>
        <span>Last updated 2026-05-06</span>
      </div>
    </aside>
  </div>
</LandingLayout>
